<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>About - Complaint Management System</title>

    <!-- External CSS -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/about.css">
</head>

<body>

<div class="container">
    <h1>About Complaint Management System</h1>

    <p>
        The <b>Complaint Management System (CMS)</b> is a web-based platform that helps users 
        register, track, and resolve complaints in a structured and efficient manner.
    </p>

    <h2>System Overview</h2>
    <p>
        The system ensures that every complaint is properly managed, assigned, and resolved 
        with transparency and accountability.
    </p>

    <h2>Complaint Assignment</h2>
    <p>
        Each complaint is assigned to a specific staff member such as a teacher, warden, 
        mess incharge, or transport staff. Only the assigned person is responsible for 
        resolving that complaint.
    </p>

    <h2>Complaint Status Flow</h2>
    <p>
        Every complaint follows a fixed status flow:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li><b>Created</b> → Complaint is registered</li>
        <li><b>Pending</b> → Waiting for action</li>
        <li><b>In Progress</b> → Work is ongoing</li>
        <li><b>Resolved</b> → Complaint is successfully solved</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="highlight">
        Once a complaint is marked as <b>Resolved</b>, an email notification is sent to the user. 
        After this stage, the complaint status cannot be changed unless permission is given by the <b>Admin</b>.
    </div>

    <h2>Email Notifications</h2>
<p>
    The system automatically sends email notifications:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>When a user signs up, a confirmation email is sent saying: <b>"You are successfully registered. Now you can use CMS."</b></li>
    
    <li>When a complaint is created, an email notification is sent to both the <b>complainer</b> and the <b>resolver</b>.</li>
    
    <li>Whenever the complaint status is updated, a notification email is sent to both the <b>complainer</b> and the <b>resolver</b> for tracking and history.</li>
    
    <li>When the complaint is resolved, a final confirmation email is sent to the user.</li>
</ul>

    <h2>OTP Verification System</h2>
    <p>
        After a complaint is marked as <b>Resolved</b>, an OTP verification process is used to confirm the resolution.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>An OTP is sent to the complainant's email.</li>
        <li>The complainant shares the OTP with the resolver.</li>
        <li>Only after OTP verification, the complaint is considered fully approved.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Complaint Filters</h2>
    <p>
        Users can filter complaints based on different categories:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><b>All</b></li>
        <li><b>Solved</b></li>
        <li><b>Unsolved</b></li>
        <li><b>Delay</b> (complaints not resolved within 7 days)</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="highlight">
        These filters are available to all users including <b>Admin, Employee, and Student</b>.
    </div>

    <h2>Admin Control & Management</h2>
    <p>
        The Admin has full control over the system and manages all operations:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Can resolve complaints directly</li>
        <li>Can delete any complaint</li>
        <li>Can reassign complaints to different resolvers</li>
        <li>Manages the complete complaint lifecycle</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        The system supports multiple users, and there is no fixed limit on the number of 
        <b>Employees, Students, or Admins</b> that can be created.
    </p>

    <h2>Complaint Resolution Policy</h2>
    <p>
        Every complaint must be resolved within <b>7 days</b> from its creation date.
    </p>

    <div class="highlight">
        If a complaint is not resolved within 7 days, it will be automatically escalated 
        to the <b>Admin</b> through a chain processing system.
    </div>

    <h2>Dashboard System</h2>
    <p>
        Each user has a personal dashboard where they can view only their own complaints 
        and related information, ensuring privacy and a better user experience.
    </p>

</div>

</body>
</html>